        11
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://touristplaces.guide/top-10-places-to-visit-in-mercerville-nature-adventure-and-history/"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Before becoming Mercerville, the community was known as Sandtown in the 18th century.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mercerville%2C_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Mercerville centers around Five Points, a historic junction where several county roads meet and commerce once thrived.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        18,
        22
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mercerville%2C_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Mercer County Park, founded in the 1970s, now preserves historic sites like the Johnson Ferry House for community use.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        5,
        4
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://touristplaces.guide/top-10-places-to-visit-in-mercerville-nature-adventure-and-history/"
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "text": "The Roebling Museum in Mercerville showcases John A. Roebling’s engineering legacy that shaped American infrastructure.",
